The code iteratively assigns each data point to the nearest centroid using Euclidean distance, 
then updates the centroid as the mean of assigned points. This process repeats until clusters stabilize.

In this project, initial centroids are manually selected from the dataset to ensure 
deterministic behavior and simplify hardware validation.

What is K?

K = number of clusters to be formed

How K is selected

K is chosen based on:

